# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY — AXIS 41 OPENS:
#   HTML PARSING / WEB SCRAPING
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This completion **OPENS AXIS 41** in the cross-language
# CLI library taxonomy: HTML Parsing / Web Scraping
# (libraries that parse HTML into a queryable DOM-like
# tree + provide CSS-selector or XPath query APIs — as
# distinct from Axis 26 Web Frameworks which SERVE
# HTML rather than parse it, or Axis 38 OpenAPI which
# parses API specs not generic HTML).
#
# Pattern: R752 120th language (Hazel) closes the prior
# 3+1 cycle → R753 Rust=96 (email-sleuth/scraper →
# Axis 41 OPENS THIS) is the first leader bump in the
# new cycle.  Pending: R754 Go=96 with a PuerkitoBio/
# goquery user; R755 TS-Node=96 with a cheeriojs/
# cheerio user; R756 121st language.
#
# WHY scraper IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-41 OPENER:
#
#   causal-agent/scraper is the canonical Rust HTML
#   parsing + CSS-selector crate.  Distinguishing
#   characteristics:
#     1. HTML5EVER FOUNDATION — built on top of
#        servo/html5ever (the Servo browser project's
#        HTML5-compliant streaming parser), giving it
#        SPEC-COMPLIANT WHATWG HTML5 parsing including
#        all the messy real-world recovery rules
#        (orphaned tags, broken attribute quoting,
#        non-conforming markup that browsers tolerate)
#     2. CSS SELECTOR QUERIES — uses servo's selectors
#        crate (the same selectors implementation used
#        by Servo's renderer) for jQuery-compatible
#        CSS selector matching: `Selector::parse("div.
#        contact-list > a.email").unwrap()`
#     3. EGO_TREE TREE STORAGE — backs the DOM with
#        the ego_tree crate (typed indices into a flat
#        Vec rather than Rc/Arc-pointer-spaghetti);
#        cache-friendly + zero-allocation tree
#        traversal
#     4. STREAMING + ZERO-COPY where possible — text
#        nodes and attributes can be borrowed as
#        &str slices into the original input buffer,
#        avoiding allocations for read-only scraping
#     5. ~2,800+ STARS ON causal-agent/scraper
#     6. ECOSYSTEM-DOMINANT — used by countless Rust
#        web-scraping CLIs: email-sleuth (this
#        completion), trieve (RAG platform),
#        languagetool-rust, nushell's HTTP plugin, the
#        xan CSV utility, mdBook, Internet Computer's
#        DFINITY tooling, etc.
#     7. SISTER CRATES — pairs with reqwest (HTTP
#        client), tokio (async runtime), and url for a
#        complete HTML-fetching-and-querying pipeline
#
# Maintained under github.com/causal-agent/scraper.
